ow?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "697.672","u": "Yes, a cow."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "698.672","u": "Nu?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "699.172","u": "We had . . . I tended [the cow] all day until night. Afterwards we left for Huta Olejska."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "706.031","u": "And the little brother was with you."},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "707.968","u": "Yes. After that, when we were in Huta Olejska . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "712.296","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "713.733","u": ". . . we went back there [where] we had been, with the Germans. I have already forgotten what the name of it is. There my brother died."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "724.467","u": "What did he die from?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "725.935","u": "Yes, yes, he died. My brother had such a stomach . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "729.560","u": "Oh."},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "730.341","u": ". . . such a large [stomach]--I do not know how it is [said] in Yiddish."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "731.857","u": "All right. Nu?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "733.295","u": "And he died. We . . . my mother . . . He told my mother that his stomach hurts him, everything hurts him, and he cannot walk. And my mother set him down, and I with the mother went for bottles. My mother went to pick . . . There were bottles there with which I could go to the gentiles . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "749.093","u": "Hm."},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "749.781","u": ". . . and bring water . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "751.000","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "751.625","u": ". . . or a little milk."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "752.906","u": "Yes. Nu?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "753.594","u": "And . . . and . . . and my brother had already died when we came from . . . and my mother had gone there. I said, &#39;You will go and pick&#39; . . . from there I used to bring a little milk . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "766.094","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "767.313","u": ". . . or water. There I would leave the bottles. I always used to say, &#39;I am . . . I feel . . . I do not need any more.&#39; I said this to the mother, because we were not supposed to be here in the forest, because the gentiles had said that we should not come, that today the police are around. And we did not go. And my mother took the bottles and went to the village[?]. And when I came [returned] the brother was already dead."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "788.815","u": "Nu?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "789.893","u": "The brother was already dead. And my mother cried so much. In the forest there are many&#226;how does one say it?&#226;[in Polish] trees?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "800.721","u": "Trees."},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "801.846","u": "Trees. So she began to do it so, with her head [she apparently demonstrates]. She had such bumps."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "807.017","u": "She beat herself . . ."},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "807.919","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "808.325","u": ". . . against the trees?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "809.044","u": "Yes. And she cried so very much. She screamed. She could not bear it. After my brother died we . . . we buried him."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "817.418","u": "Who buried him?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "819.101","u": "I with the mother."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "819.944","u": "You with the mother?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "821.413","u": "Yes, I with the mother."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "821.960","u": "In the forest?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "822.491","u": "Yes, in the forest. Nothing, just dug such a tiny grave. He was only three years old. He was very small. And afterwards I remained with the mother. The mother cried very much. [short break in the wire] . . . very much. My mother was badly emaciated [?]. My mother did not get better, because my mother cried very much. She was so thin as this, as a stick. And afterwards I went with my mother another month, [or] two. I was with the mother another two months. And my mother died."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "852.528","u": "Where?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "853.247","u": "My mother died."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "853.747","u": "In the forest?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "854.247","u": "Yes, in the forest. Everything in the forest, because I was in the forest three years [words not clear]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "859.779","u": "Aha."},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "860.639","u": "Two and a half [years], not three."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "861.967","u": "[In whispers] You must go?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "865.912","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "866.490","u": "We shall talk again later, yes?"},    {"who": "Raisel Meltzak", "start": "868.724","u": "Yes."}        ]
